### Event Schema Evolution

Use semantic versioning and schema registries (e.g., Avro, Protobuf) to track schema changes. Support backward and forward compatibility by making new fields optional and deprecating old ones gracefully. Consumers handle multiple versions simultaneously or transform old events during replay.

```typescript
interface OrderCreatedEvent {
  version: number; // 1, 2, 3...
  orderId: string;
  customerId: string;
  items: OrderItem[]; // Added in v2
  totalAmount?: number; // Added in v3, optional for older
}

function normalizeEvent(event: OrderCreatedEvent): OrderCreatedEventV3 {
  return {
    ...event,
    version: 3,
    totalAmount: event.totalAmount || calculateTotal(event.items)
  };
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Treating schema evolution as only adding optional fields—deleting fields breaks old producers, and breaking changes require dual-write periods.

